Rmd
Move files to a directory like /home/trash which you don't need them
and you can also recover them.
How to use
$rmd filename
move filename to /home/trash
$rmd -r filename
recover filename to its former path

=====>2011-10-7<=====
rmd-0.1
move and recover

rmd-0.2
update log file when recover

=====>2011-10-8<=====
rmd update
time limit to remove too old files in trash

=====>2011-10-11<=====
